## Goal

**Feature Goal**: Implement the robust output-parsing pipeline (PRD §12.9) that turns an agent's raw stdout into a clean commit message, reading ONLY three Manifest fields (Output, JSONField, StripCodeFence). The pipeline: trim → optional code-fence unwrap → raw/json switch with graceful JSON fallback → newline normalization → final trim. It is the parser half of the provider subsystem and the inner component of the generate parse-correction loop.

**Deliverable**: Two new files in the EXISTING `package provider` (created by P1.M2.T1.S1):
- `internal/provider/parse.go` — plain `package provider` line (the package doc is owned by manifest.go; do NOT repeat `// Package provider`) + the unexported `func parseOutput(raw string, m Manifest) (string, bool)` + an unexported `extractJSON` helper + a package-level newline-collapse regexp + godoc citing PRD §12.9/§17.4.
- `internal/provider/parse_test.go` — `package provider` (WHITE-BOX, because parseOutput is unexported) table-driven tests using stdlib `testing` only, covering all contract cases.

**Success Definition**: `go test ./internal/provider/` passes the table (raw clean, fenced-raw, fenced-raw-with-langtag, tilde fence, fenced-json, json-embedded-in-prose, malformed-json→fallback-to-raw, json-non-string-field→fallback, newline normalization, fence-strip-off keeps fence, empty→("",false), whitespace-only→("",false)). `go build ./internal/provider/`, `go vet ./internal/provider/` clean; `gofmt -l internal/provider/` empty. stdlib-only imports (encoding/json, regexp, strings). No go.mod/go.sum change; manifest.go/manifest_test.go/main.go/Makefile/internal/ui untouched; no import cycle.

## Why

- **The robustness centerpiece of output handling.** PRD §17.4 (decisions D1) deliberately switched from commit-pi's fragile JSON+sed contract to a RAW default ("output only the message") because raw has nothing to escape/parse and removes the "no double quotes in the message" constraint. §12.9 is the cleanup pipeline that makes raw reliable: it tolerates a model wrapping output in a code fence, tolerates preamble around JSON, and NEVER hard-fails on a parse glitch — it falls back to the cleaned raw stdout.
- **Pure + table-testable.** parseOutput takes a string + a Manifest and returns (string, bool); it does no I/O, imports no os/exec/log/config. That makes the full behavior verifiable with a byte-exact table — no process spawning. (Verified by a throwaway prototype: all 12 contract + edge cases pass; see research note §6.)
- **Consumed by the generate parse-correction loop (P1.M6.T1.S1).** The inner loop calls parseOutput on agent stdout; `ok==false` triggers one corrective retry; `ok==true` yields the message. Getting this byte-exact now unblocks M6 and the executor (M2.T4.S1).

