1. NEW file `internal/provider/parse.go`, plain `package provider` line (NOT the package doc — manifest.go owns `// Package provider`; a second package-comment is a vet/lint error). Imports: stdlib ONLY — `encoding/json`, `regexp`, `strings`. NO `os`, `log`, `fmt` (parseOutput returns ok=false on failure, never an error), NO config/cobra/go-toml.
2. Package-level regexp var (compile once): `var collapseNewlines = regexp.MustCompile(` + "`" + `\n{3,}` + "`" + `)` — collapses 3+ consecutive `\n` to exactly 2.
3. **`func parseOutput(raw string, m Manifest) (string, bool)`** implementing §12.9 byte-exactly (see Implementation Blueprint for the full listing). Reads ONLY `m.Output`, `m.JSONField`, `m.StripCodeFence`; ignores every other Manifest field. Returns `(msg, ok)` where `ok = msg != ""`.
